name: The Dinner
description:
IT ALL BEGAN WITH THE HUNGER...A HUNGER I FELT WITHIN THAT SOMEHOW NEVER FULFILLED MY HARROWING DESIRES, UNTIL SHE TOLD ME THAT NOTHING WOULD OVERCOME THAT URGE EXCEPT FOR HUMAN FLESH. THAT NIGHT WE CONSUMED OUR BEAUTIFUL CHILD...
I FEEL HIM NOW EVEN CLOSER WITHIN ME, BEATING INSIDE MY CHEST, NEXT TO MY HEART. EVERY DAY SHE PREPARES A NEW SOMEONE, Killing a new urge inside of me, yet growing another...I SOMETIMES FEEL WE NOW CARRY MANY FEELINGS OF SO MANY INSIDE OF US.

I REMEMBER THAT SHE WASN'T LIKE THIS BEFORE...WE WEREN'T LIKE THIS...THE ONLY THING THAT CHANGED HER WAS THAT NIGHT SHE SAW SOMEONE IN THE MIRROR.

I NEVER SAW THAT SOMEONE...
